<% content_for :page_id do %>home<% end %>
<div class="container">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <h1>Protecting Our River</h1>

    <p>
    Protecting Our River is a community engagement project that mobilizes L.A.
    residents from a variety of backgrounds to help monitor the biodiversity of
    the L.A. River and its tributaries. We aim to increase community awareness
    and participation in conservation of biodiversity by merging science, art,
    and community involvement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="col-md-4">
    <figure>
      <%= image_tag 'river/blue_heron_plants.jpg', class: "img-responsive" %>
      <figcaption><span class="meta">Â© NHMLA Community Science Program, some rights reserved (CC-BY-NC)</span></figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="our-work">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Biodiversity Monitoring</h2>

    <div class="col-md-8">
      <p>
        We use a variety of methods to collect
        biodiversity data including photographic
        observations and environmental DNA (the DNA organisms shed into the
        environment).
      </p>
      <p>
        For our summer 2019 pilot program, we collected 52 sediment
        and water samples from two locations along the river. For 2020-2021,
        we will have three rounds of sampling from twelve locations.
        UCLA researchers examined the environmental DNA (eDNA) in the samples
        to identify the microbes, fungi, plants, and animals in the area.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <ul>
        <li><%= pluralize(@stats[:locations], 'L.A. river location') %></li>
        <li><%= pluralize(@stats[:sites], 'sampling site') %></li>
        <li><%= pluralize(@stats[:taxa], 'identified organism') %></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


